      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING NANGAR (1) overcame a check to place in a Grade 4/5 at this track over 520m latest, finishing a 2 length second (30.30). Has box 1 this time where he has two wins. Should be in this for a long way. CATCH THE FEELS (5) was a strong winner (30.09) from box 5 last time, scoring by 2.25 lengths at this track. Has the squeeze box to overcome and will need the breaks early. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Can measure up again. RAPIDO KUNA (2) had a tough draw to overcome and was game in defeat when only 0.8 lengths from West On Harry in second (27.48) at Mandurah. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Expecting another good run. MYLES KEEPING (3) warrants respect following a recent placing at big odds.",
